{"title_page": "Sex trafficking in Vietnam", "text_new": "'''Sex trafficking in Vietnam''' is [[human trafficking]] for the purpose of [[Sexual slavery|sexual exploitation and slavery]] that occurs in the [[Socialist Republic of Vietnam]]. Vietnam is a source and, to a lesser extent, destination country for sexually trafficked persons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://un-act.org/vietnam/|title=VIET NAM - UN ACT|website=UN-ACT}}</ref>\n\nSex trafficking victims in the country are from all [[List of ethnic groups in Vietnam|ethnic groups in Vietnam]] and foreigners. Vietnamese citizens, primarily women and girls, have been sex trafficked into other countries in [[Asia]] and different [[continents]].<ref name=autogenerated8>{{cite web|url=https://www.rfa.org/english/news/vietnam/trafficking-03282013190106.html|title=Vietnamese Women Fall Prey to Sex Racket|date=March 8, 2013|website=Radio Free Asia}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.antislavery.org/vietnamese-children-trafficked-europe/|title=Precarious journeys of Vietnamese children trafficked to Europe|date=March 7, 2019|website=Anti-slavery International}}</ref> They are forced into prostitution, marriages, and or pregnancies.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asianews.it/news-en/Women,-children-and-babies:-human-trafficking-to-China-is-on-the-rise-47513.html|title=Women, children and babies: human trafficking to China is on the rise|date=July 11, 2019|website=Asia News}}</ref><ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://thediplomat.com/2019/11/vietnams-human-trafficking-problem-is-too-big-to-ignore/|title=Vietnam's Human Trafficking Problem Is Too Big to Ignore|date=November 8, 2019|website=The Diplomat}}</ref> Victims are threatened<ref name=\"auto3\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/cnainsider/vietnam-kidnapped-brides-trafficking-china-wives-11777162|title=Raped, beaten and sold in China: Vietnam's kidnapped young brides|date=August 3, 2019|website=Channel News Asia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-04-21/vietnam-sapa-women-trafficked-to-china/9675610|title=Vietnamese teen's escape from the China trafficking trade that sold her mother|date=September 18, 2018|website=ABC News}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated4>{{cite web|url=https://focustaiwan.tw/society/201911180020|title=Sex trafficking ring busted, Vietnamese women rescued|date=November 18, 2019|website=Focus Taiwan}}</ref> and physically and psychologically harmed.<ref name=autogenerated5>{{cite web|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/sold-raped-enslaved-human-trafficking-victims-shared-stories-in-2019-4030004.html|title=Sold, raped, enslaved: Human trafficking victims shared stories in 2019|date=December 24, 2019|website=VnExpress}}</ref> They contract [[sexually transmitted diseases]] from rapes, and abuse<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asianews.it/news-en/Vietnams-modern-sex-slaves-sold-in-China-as-prostitutes-or-brides-33361.html|title=Vietnam's \"modern sex slaves\" sold in China as prostitutes or brides|date=February 3, 2015|website=Asia News}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated9>{{cite web|url=https://www.voanews.com/east-asia/vietnamese-trafficking-victim-reveals-heartbreaking-ordeal|title=Vietnamese Trafficking Victim Reveals Heartbreaking Ordeal|date=September 24, 2015|website=VOA News}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated8 /> and malnutrition are common. Some women and girls are tortured and or murdered.\n\nSex trafficking and exploitation have pervaded all levels of Vietnamese society. Male and female perpetrators in Vietnam come from a wide range of backgrounds and a number are members of or facilitated by organized crime syndicates and gangs.<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref name=\"auto3\"/>\n<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.antislavery.org/vietnamese-trafficking/|title=Dangerous journeys: tackling Vietnamese trafficking|date=September 5, 2018|website=Anti-slavery International}}</ref><ref name=\"auto3\"/>\n<ref name=\"auto\"/> Some government officials, troops, and police, as well as foreigners, have been complicit in sex trafficking in Vietnam.\n\nThe extent of sex trafficking in Vietnam is unknown because of the lack of data, the underground nature of sex trafficking crimes, inadequate victim identification procedures, and other elements.\n<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|url=http://hanoitimes.vn/human-trafficking-remains-a-headache-in-vietnam-and-southeast-asia-4046.html|title=Human trafficking remains a headache in Vietnam and Southeast Asia|date=June 22, 2018|website=Hanoi Times}}</ref> The enforcement of sex trafficking laws and investigating and prosecuting of cases have been hindered by corruption, apathy, border management problems, lack of cooperation among sectors, ignorance of anti-trafficking law, and more.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/asia-pacific/human-trafficking-on-rise-in-vietnam-says-government/722008|title=Human trafficking on rise in Vietnam, says government|date=July 1, 2017|website=Anadolu Agency}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated1 /> [[Globalization]] and the  [[ASEAN|Association of Southeast Asian Nations\u2019(ASEAN)]] shift towards a formal community with freer movement of trade and capital may lead to an increase sex trafficking.<ref name=autogenerated6>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-vietnam-humantrafficking/trafficking-of-vietnamese-women-for-sex-and-marriage-expands-across-region-expert-idUSKCN0Y9180|title=Trafficking of Vietnamese women for sex and marriage expands across region: expert|date=May 18, 2016|website=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20160518101650-vj7xq/|title=Trafficking of Vietnamese women for sex and marriage expands across region - expert|date=May 18, 2016|website=Thomson Reuters Foundation News}}</ref>\n\n==Victims==\n[[File:VietnameseProvincesMapTiengViet1.png|upright=1.4|thumbnail|right|Vietnamese women and girls are sex trafficked into and out of all [[provinces of Vietnam]].]] \n\nVietnamese women and girls are sex trafficked into [[China]],<ref name=autogenerated3>{{cite web|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/china-is-main-destination-for-vietnamese-trafficking-victims-official-3797546.html|title=China is main destination for Vietnamese trafficking victims: official|date=August 24, 2018|website=VnExpress}}</ref><ref name=\"auto4\" /> [[Cambodia]],<ref name=autogenerated6 /> [[Malaysia]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://doynews.com/tags/sex-trafficking-vietnam|title=Sex trafficking in Vietnam|website=Doy News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thanhniennews.com/society/136-vietnamese-women-rescued-from-forced-prostitution-in-kuala-lumpur-37137.html|title=136 Vietnamese women rescued from forced prostitution in Kuala Lumpur|date=January 4, 2015|website=Thanhnien News}}</ref> the [[Philippines]], [[Taiwan]],<ref name=autogenerated4 />, [[South Korea]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thanhniennews.com/society/6-arrested-including-2-foreigners-for-selling-147-vietnamese-women-to-skorea-china-33134.html|title=6 arrested, including 2 foreigners, for selling 147 Vietnamese women to S.Korea, China|date=October 26, 2014|website=Thanhnien News}}</ref> and other nations. They are forced into prostitution or marriages, as well as [[unfree labour]] in homes and on farms.<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref name=\"auto3\"/> A number of women are raped so they become pregnant and are forced to be surrogates.<ref name=\"auto2\"/> Some women and girls have been trafficked to groups of men, who are poor and pool their money together to buy one wife.<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite web|url=https://vietcetera.com/en/pacific-links-foundation-the-battle-against-human-trafficking/|title=Pacific Links Foundation: The Battle Against Human Trafficking|date=August 7, 2017|website=Vietcetera}}</ref> Forced prostitutes are raped in brothels, massage parlors, karaoke bars, and other establishments.<ref name=autogenerated3 /> They are kept under strict surveliance and it is not uncommon for them to be guarded and or tied or locked up.<ref name=autogenerated9 /> A number of victims are drugged.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/vietnamese-woman-trafficked-to-china-returns-home-after-22-years-3947636.html|title=Vietnamese woman trafficked to China returns home after 22 years|date=July 4, 2019|website=VnExpress}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated5 /> \n\nMinorities and people in poverty with little education and awareness of trafficking, as well as children,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2016/04/17/asia/vietnamese-girls-child-brides-china/index.html|title=Vietnamese girls smuggled into China and sold as child brides|date=April 19, 2016|website=CNN}}</ref> are vulnerable to sex traffikcing.<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref name=\"auto4\"/><ref name=\"auto3\"/><ref name=autogenerated3 /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thanhniennews.com/society/4-arrested-for-forcing-women-into-sex-ring-in-northern-vietnam-62554.html|title=4 arrested for forcing women into sex ring in northern Vietnam|date=May 25, 2016|website=Thanhnien News}}</ref>\n\nVictims face social stigma after escaping or being rescued. Some are reluctant to report traffickers to the local authorities because they fear reprisal from the criminals.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://thediplomat.com/2019/11/vietnams-human-trafficking-problem-is-too-big-to-ignore/|title=Vietnam's Human Trafficking Problem Is Too Big to Ignore|date=November 8, 2019|website=The Diplomat}}</ref>\n\nVietnamese victims have been sex trafficked to businesses catering to people seeing the [[Southeast Asian Games]] and other sporting events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/lifestyle-culture/article/3041328/sea-games-foreign-tourist-surge-philippines-sees-rising|title=SEA Games: foreign tourist surge to Philippines sees rising risk of sex trafficking|date=December 10, 2019|website=South China Morning Post}}</ref>\n\n==Perpetrators==\nThe perpetrators are often members of or collude with organized criminal groups.<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref name=\"auto3\"/> Some perpetrators are government officials, military officers or enlisted men, or police. Loan sharks have been involved in sex trafficking as well and take advantage of debt bondage to control their victims.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> The traffickers are sometimes the victims' family members or friends. Perpetrators are motivated by monetary incentives.<ref name=autogenerated2 /> A number of perpetrators are coerced victims of trafficking themselves.<ref name=autogenerated3 />\n\nSome sex traffickers pose as police officers to gain victims' trust.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/80-percent-of-vietnamese-human-trafficking-victims-end-up-in-china-3960605.html|title=80 percent of Vietnamese human trafficking victims end up in China|date=August 1, 2019|website=VnExpress International}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated3 /> Traffickers use chat sites and social networks such as Facebook and Zalo, a popular Vietnamese messaging app.<ref name=autogenerated3 /><ref name=autogenerated7>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenewhumanitarian.org/news/2016/09/02/vietnam-wakes-its-human-trafficking-problem|title=Vietnam wakes up to its human trafficking problem|date=September 2, 2016|website=The New Humanitarian}}</ref> Traffickers threaten victims' families to ensure submission.\n \n==Government response problems==\nThe government had inadequate re-integration services, therapeutic support, legal and financial assistance, and education for victims. Limited protections are available for women and girls returned to their homes.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> \n \n==Non-governmental organizations==\n[[Blue Dragon Children's Foundation]] rescues and restores sex trafficked victims in the country.<ref name=autogenerated5 /><ref name=autogenerated7 /> It is supported by the [[United Nations]] Trust Fund for Victims of Human Trafficking.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unodc.org/unodc/en/human-trafficking-fund/human-trafficking-fund_grants-facility.html|title=Our Funded Projects Around the World|website=United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime}}</ref> \n\nPacific Links Foundation is an organization working to end sex trafficking in Vietnam through education and economic empowerment.<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Vietnam topics}}\n{{Sex trafficking in Southeast Asia|state=collapsed}}\n{{Asia in topic|Sex trafficking in}}\n{{Sex trafficking|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Vietnamese society]]\n[[Category:Crime in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Human rights in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Prostitution in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Sex industry in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Violence in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Violence against women in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Women in Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Sex trafficking by country|Vietnam]]\n", "text_old": "'''Sex trafficking in Vietnam''' is [[human trafficking]] for the purpose of [[Sexual slavery|sexual exploitation and slavery]] that occurs in the [[Socialist Republic of Vietnam]]. Vietnam is a source and, to a lesser extent, destination country for sexually trafficked persons.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://un-act.org/vietnam/|title=VIET NAM - UN ACT|website=UN-ACT}}</ref>\n\nSex trafficking victims in the country are from all [[List of ethnic groups in Vietnam|ethnic groups in Vietnam]] and foreigners. Vietnamese citizens, primarily women and girls, have been sex trafficked into other countries in [[Asia]] and different [[continents]].<ref name=autogenerated8>{{cite web|url=https://www.rfa.org/english/news/vietnam/trafficking-03282013190106.html|title=Vietnamese Women Fall Prey to Sex Racket|date=March 8, 2013|website=Radio Free Asia}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.antislavery.org/vietnamese-children-trafficked-europe/|title=Precarious journeys of Vietnamese children trafficked to Europe|date=March 7, 2019|website=Anti-slavery International}}</ref> They are forced into prostitution, marriages, and or pregnancies.<ref name=\"aut