rced into prostitution or marriages, as well as [[unfree labour]] in homes and on farms.<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref name=\"auto3\"/> A number of women are raped so they become pregnant and are forced to be surrogates.<ref name=\"auto2\"/> Some women and girls have been trafficked to groups of men, who are poor and pool their money together to buy one wife.<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite web|url=https://vietcetera.com/en/pacific-links-foundation-the-battle-against-human-trafficking/|title=Pacific Links Foundation: The Battle Against Human Trafficking|date=August 7, 2017|website=Vietcetera}}</ref> Forced prostitutes are raped in brothels, massage parlors, karaoke bars, and other establishments.<ref name=autogenerated3 /> They are kept under strict surveliance and it is not uncommon for them to be guarded and or tied or locked up.<ref name=autogenerated9 /> A number of victims are drugged.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://e.vnexpress.net/news/news/vietnamese-woman-trafficked-to-china-returns-home-after-22-years-3947636.html|title=Vietnamese woman trafficked to China returns home after 22 years|date=July 4, 2019|website=VnExpress}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated5 /> \n\nMinorities and people in poverty with little education and awareness of trafficking, as well as children,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2016/04/17/asia/vietnamese-girls-child-brides-china/index.html|title=Vietnamese girls smuggled into China and sold as child brides|date=April 19, 2016|website=CNN}}</ref> are vulnerable to sex traffikcing.<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref name=\"auto4\"/><ref name=\"auto3\"/><ref name=autogenerated3 /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thanhniennews.com/society/4-arrested-for-forcing-women-into-sex-ring-in-northern-vietnam-62554.html|title=4 arrested for forcing women into sex ring in northern Vietnam|date=May 25, 2016|website=Thanhnien News}}</ref>\n\nVictims face social stigma after escaping or being rescued. Some are reluctant to report traffickers to the local authorities because